            <ObservedData>
              <Attribute Type="Description">In 2 sisters, born of consanguineous Syrian parents (family 1), with neurodevelopmental disorder with hypotonia, facial dysmorphism, and brain abnormalities (NEDHFBA; 619383), Rehman et al. (2019) identified a homozygous 1-bp deletion (c.347delT, NM_001135629.2) in exon 4 of the PPP1R21 gene, resulting in a frameshift and premature termination (Ile116LysfsTer25). The mutation, which was found by exome sequencing and confirmed by Sanger sequencing, segregated with the disorder in the family. It was not present in public databases, including gnomAD. Family history revealed 2 additional affected sibs who had died of the disease; genetic material was not available for study. Functional studies of the variant and studies of patient cells were not performed.</Attribute>
